CatDescriptText: H. McCaskill, owner, Village Fruit Market, 2204 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?" Answer reads: "If both parties had searched more carefully, they could have picked better candidates."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of H. McCaskill wearing cap, eyeglasses, and short sleeved checked shirt, standing on sidewalk leaning against light colored car parked in street, possibly Centre Avenue
